         b'ys:</span>\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class="comment-meta commentmeta'
         b'data"><a href="http://mobblog.cs.ucl.ac.uk/2008/01/18/search-engines'
         b'-and-mediocre-students/#comment-1641">\n\t\t\tJanuary 19, 2008 at 11'
         b':02 pm</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<blockquote><p>Do search engines do a '
         b'bad job at capturing the quality of information?</p></blockquote'
         b'>\n<p>\nI&#8217;m not sure that&#8217;s what she&#8217;s saying; s'
         b'earch engines are good at finding information but they don&#8217;t t'
         b'each you how to do research. The point of an assignment is not to fi'
         b'nd the answer but to learn <i>how</i> to find the answer. Most under'
         b'graduate assignments can probably be answered using Google and Wikip'
         b'edia, but hopefully at some point in their careers the students will'
         b' come across a question that can&#8217;t, and at that point they&#82'
         b'17;ll need skills like critically evaluating and comparing sources, '
         b'following references, understanding information in its historical co'
         b'ntext, etc etc. By forcing her students to cite their sources the pr'
         b'ofessor is forcing them to acquire those skills.</p>\n\n\t\t<div cla'
         b'ss="reply">\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</li><!-- #comm'
