         b'class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://mobblog.cs.ucl.'
         b'ac.uk/2008/01/18/search-engines-and-mediocre-students/#comment-1643"'
         b'>\n\t\t\tJanuary 20, 2008 at 12:28 pm</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<p>Inst'
         b'ead of spending time on her crusade against Google, Wikipedia, and h'
         b'er students, she may well spend time thinking about better problems '
         b'for her undegrads. There are many problems that require the use of c'
         b'ritical thinking, and for which Wikipedia, Google, and (even) smelly'
         b' books are not enough. Unfortunately, only good teachers who are gre'
         b'at researchers are able to do so. &#8220;Search Engines and Mediocre'
         b' Students&#8221;? What about &#8220;Search Engines and Mediocre Teac'
